        "title": "Relationships: seurustella, olla yhes, jättää",
        "summary": "The relationship vocabulary gossip runs on: deittailla (to date around), seurustella (to be in a relationship), olla yhes (be together), mennä kihloihin (get engaged), jättää (to dump), erota (to break up). 'Yhes' is spoken 'yhdessä' - and yes, 'iskeä' means both to strike and to pick someone up.",
        "examples": [
            "Ne on oltu yhes jo vuoden. = They've been together for a year already.",
            "Eka treffit meni tosi hyvin. = The first date went really well.",
            "Se jätti mut tekstiviestillä. = They dumped me by text."
        ]
    },
